Implementation summary:
- `MessageEnvelope` is a `readonly record struct` with positional members
  (`ProtocolVersion`, `Kind`, `Topic`, `CorrelationId`, `TimestampUnixMs`,
  `Payload(JsonElement)`) per design.md §"MessageEnvelope contract" and Req 3.1 / 3.6 /
  3.8. Payload is a `System.Text.Json.JsonElement` so the codec can preserve unknown
  fields (Req 3.7) without forcing an early type binding.
- `MessageKind` enum exposes the 4 envelope kinds (`State`=0, `Event`=1, `Request`=2,
  `Response`=3) used to drive the dispatch queue's coalesce / FIFO / correlation
  paths.
- `ConnectionState` enum exposes the 5 transport-layer states
  (`Disconnected`=0, `Connecting`=1, `Connected`=2, `Reconnecting`=3,
  `PermanentlyDisconnected`=4) consumed by `ConnectionStateMachine` and
  `IConnectionDiagnostics`.
- `RuntimeState` enum exposes the 5 runtime lifecycle states
  (`NotInitialized`=0, `Initializing`=1, `Running`=2, `ShuttingDown`=3,
  `Disposed`=4) consumed by `ICoreIpcRuntime.State`.
- `csc.rsp` in `Runtime/Abstractions/` pins `-langversion:10` so that
  `record struct` (a C# 10 feature) compiles under the Unity 6.3 / Roslyn
  toolchain regardless of editor defaults.
- `Runtime/Plugins/SystemTextJson/` ships `System.Text.Json` 8.0.5 + its native
  transitive deps (`System.Text.Encodings.Web`,
  `System.Runtime.CompilerServices.Unsafe`, `Microsoft.Bcl.AsyncInterfaces`).
  These are required because `JsonElement` is referenced from the
  `Abstractions` asmdef. The plugins live inside the package so they ship
  with the UPM artifact.
- `AbstractionsReferenceCheck.cs` (internal, in the `Core` asmdef) creates a
  sample `MessageEnvelope` and references `MessageKind`, `ConnectionState`,
  `RuntimeState`. This satisfies the task's observable completion criterion
  ("each enum and record struct is exported from `Abstractions` and
  resolvable from `Core`") at compile time, ensuring the asmdef wiring stays
  honest as later tasks add real consumers.

